<!-- Async WordPress.com Remote Login -->
<script id="wpcom_remote_login_js">
var wpcom_remote_login_extra_auth = '';
function wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( element_id ) {
	var dom_node = document.getElementById( element_id );
	if ( dom_node ) { dom_node.remove(); }
}
function wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_classes( class_name ) {
	var dom_nodes = document.querySelectorAll( '.' + class_name );
	for ( var i = 0; i < dom_nodes.length; i++ ) {
		dom_nodes[i].remove();
	}
}
function wpcom_remote_login_final_cleanup() {
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_classes( "wpcom_remote_login_msg" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_key" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_validate" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_js" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_request_access_iframe" );
	wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_request_access_styles" );
}

// Watch for messages back from the remote login
window.addEventListener( "message", function( e ) {
	if ( e.origin === "https://r-login.wordpress.com" ) {
		var data = {};
		try {
			data = JSON.parse( e.data );
		} catch( e ) {
			wpcom_remote_login_final_cleanup();
			return;
		}

		if ( data.msg === 'LOGIN' ) {
			// Clean up the login check iframe
			wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( "wpcom_remote_login_key" );

			var id_regex = new RegExp( /^[0-9]+$/ );
			var token_regex = new RegExp( /^.*|.*|.*$/ );
			if (
				token_regex.test( data.token )
				&& id_regex.test( data.wpcomid )
			) {
				// We have everything we need to ask for a login
				var script = document.createElement( "script" );
				script.setAttribute( "id", "wpcom_remote_login_validate" );
				script.src = '/remote-login.php?wpcom_remote_login=validate'
					+ '&wpcomid=' + data.wpcomid
					+ '&token=' + encodeURIComponent( data.token )
					+ '&host=' + window.location.protocol
						+ '//' + window.location.hostname;
				document.body.appendChild( script );
			}

			return;
		}

		// Safari ITP, not logged in, so redirect
		if ( data.msg === 'LOGIN-REDIRECT' ) {
			window.location = 'https://wordpress.com/log-in?redirect_to=' + window.location.href;
			return;
		}

		// Safari ITP, storage access failed, remove the request
		if ( data.msg === 'LOGIN-REMOVE' ) {
			var css_zap = 'html { -webkit-transition: margin-top 1s; transition: margin-top 1s; } /* 9001 */ html { margin-top: 0 !important; } * html body { margin-top: 0 !important; } @media screen and ( max-width: 782px ) { html { margin-top: 0 !important; } * html body { margin-top: 0 !important; } }';
			var style_zap = document.createElement( 'style' );
			style_zap.type = 'text/css';
			style_zap.appendChild( document.createTextNode( css_zap ) );
			document.body.appendChild( style_zap );

			var e = document.getElementById( 'wpcom_request_access_iframe' );
			e.parentNode.removeChild( e );

			document.cookie = 'wordpress_com_login_access=denied; path=/; max-age=31536000';

			return;
		}

		// Safari ITP
		if ( data.msg === 'REQUEST_ACCESS' ) {
			console.log( 'request access: safari' );

			// Check ITP iframe enable/disable knob
			if ( wpcom_remote_login_extra_auth !== 'safari_itp_iframe' ) {
				return;
			}

			// If we are in a "private window" there is no ITP.
			var private_window = false;
			try {
				var opendb = window.openDatabase( null, null, null, null );
			} catch( e ) {
				private_window = true;
			}

			if ( private_window ) {
				console.log( 'private window' );
				return;
			}

			var iframe = document.createElement( 'iframe' );
			iframe.id = 'wpcom_request_access_iframe';
			iframe.setAttribute( 'scrolling', 'no' );
			iframe.setAttribute( 'sandbox', 'allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation' );
			iframe.src = 'https://r-login.wordpress.com/remote-login.php?wpcom_remote_login=request_access&origin=' + encodeURIComponent( data.origin ) + '&wpcomid=' + encodeURIComponent( data.wpcomid );

			var css = 'html { -webkit-transition: margin-top 1s; transition: margin-top 1s; } /* 9001 */ html { margin-top: 46px !important; } * html body { margin-top: 46px !important; } @media screen and ( max-width: 660px ) { html { margin-top: 71px !important; } * html body { margin-top: 71px !important; } #wpcom_request_access_iframe { display: block; height: 71px !important; } } #wpcom_request_access_iframe { border: 0px; height: 46px; position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; min-width: 100%; z-index: 99999; background: #23282d; } ';

			var style = document.createElement( 'style' );
			style.type = 'text/css';
			style.id = 'wpcom_request_access_styles';
			style.appendChild( document.createTextNode( css ) );
			document.body.appendChild( style );

			document.body.appendChild( iframe );
		}

		if ( data.msg === 'DONE' ) {
			wpcom_remote_login_final_cleanup();
		}
	}
}, false );

// Inject the remote login iframe after the page has had a chance to load
// more critical resources
window.addEventListener( "DOMContentLoaded", function( e ) {
	var iframe = document.createElement( "iframe" );
	iframe.style.display = "none";
	iframe.setAttribute( "scrolling", "no" );
	iframe.setAttribute( "id", "wpcom_remote_login_key" );
	iframe.src = "https://r-login.wordpress.com/remote-login.php"
		+ "?wpcom_remote_login=key"
		+ "&origin=aHR0cHM6Ly9ibGFja2xpc3RkZWNsYXNzaWZpZWQubmV0"
		+ "&wpcomid=9473618"
		+ "&time=1603817404";
	document.body.appendChild( iframe );
}, false );
</script>

		function addLoadEvent(func) {
			var oldonload = window.onload;
			if (typeof window.onload != 'function') {
				window.onload = func;
			} else {
				window.onload = function () {
					oldonload();
					func();
				}
			}
		}

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:1 Louis T Steinhil (‚Ññ 27)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 10/4/2019 in the US<br />
Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-9Rj" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-9Rj</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/32Xpd34" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/32Xpd34</a><br />
&nbsp; </p></div>
<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
&nbsp;<br />
<b>Director:</b> Bill <b>Roe</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> John <b>Eisendrath</b>, Jon <b>Bokenkamp</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="38143" data-permalink="https://blacklistdeclassified.net/%f0%9f%94%b4-ye-olde-photo-workshoppe/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477/" data-orig-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477-e1570427951243.jpeg" data-orig-size="655,387" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="55E93BBF-B31B-4473-845F-5434894BF477" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477-e1570427951243.jpeg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477-e1570427951243.jpeg?w=655" src="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477-e1570427951243.jpeg?w=655&#038;h=387" alt="" width="655" height="387" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-38143" srcset="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477-e1570427951243.jpeg 655w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477-e1570427951243.jpeg?w=150&amp;h=89 150w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/55e93bbf-b31b-4473-845f-5434894bf477-e1570427951243.jpeg?w=300&amp;h=177 300w" sizes="(max-width: 655px) 100vw, 655px" /><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): Red has been abducted ‚Äì by Katarina Rostova, Liz‚Äôs mother and notorious KGB/Cabal operative and <i>femme fatale</i>. Having found out that Ressler had stirred up Russian interest in her by his search for her, Red reached out to a friend (‚Äúmystery man‚Äù) who located Katarina living in Paris. Red found her walking alone along a dark Parisian street on a rainy night and called her name. She turned and recognized him, ‚ÄúRaymond.‚Äù She walked up to him and kissed him, deeply. ‚ÄúAre they watching?‚Äù she asked. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs not safe. You‚Äôre not safe,‚Äù he answered, followed by another deep kiss. Then she took out a hypodermic needle and jabbed him in the gut with it. He looked at the needle, then collapsed. A car drove up, two men got out of it, loaded Red into it and drove off. Katarina picked up his fedora and, twiddling it, walked on, smiling slightly.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Red has been friends with the mystery man since childhood. Not only did the mystery man cast doubt on the story Dom told to Liz about Ilya Koslov‚Äôs past with Katarina, he looks a little like an older Ilya himself. Not only do both he and Red know Dom, both refer to Liz as ‚ÄúMasha,‚Äù and both agree it was concerning that Dom told Liz ‚Äúthat story.‚Äù According to Dom‚Äôs account to Liz, Red was in fact Ilya Koslov before taking on the identity of Raymond Reddington. The reason Red gives for Dom‚Äôs story was that Dom wanted Liz to be able ‚Äúto move on.‚Äù And in fact Liz has moved on, with her daughter Agnes, now about four, coming back home to live.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
The Season 6 ‚Äúplot against America‚Äù uncovered by former MI6 agent Christopher Miles turned out not to be a plot to assassinate the President at all but rather a plot by the President to assassinate the First Lady, who wanted him to come clean about a drunken car accident four years earlier that had killed a woman and her son. Liz and Ressler interrupted the shooting just in time to throw off Mr Sandquist‚Äôs shot, but Sandquist turned the tables and accused them of being the assassins, so they were arrested. (They had just earlier escaped from the Post Office along with Aram and Cooper in a break-out masterminded by Liz.) Red intervened by ramming the police wagon they were in and, after a shootout, Anna McMahon was just about to execute Red when Dembe(!) appeared and shot McMahon. So Dembe is back! ‚ÄúI said I needed to follow my own path. I did. It led me back to you.‚Äù But more trouble is in store. Dembe tells Red ‚ÄúOur friend in Miami says the Townsend Directive is in play,‚Äù so it‚Äôs possible being held captive by Katarina Rostova may not be the worst of Red‚Äôs problems.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>

<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ The hospital ]<br />
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ] [ An inspector with the French internal security service <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_Directorate_for_Internal_Security">DGSI</a> , Ren√© Oban, gets off the elevator and walks past hospital personnel to Red‚Äôs room] [ DISTORTED, INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]<br />

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:2 Louis T Steinhil, Pt 2 (‚Ññ 27)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 10/11/2019 in the US<br />
Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-9VO" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-9VO</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/2IKMXzF" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2IKMXzF</a><br />

&nbsp;<br />
<b>Directed by:</b> Cort <b>Hessler</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Lukas <b>Reiter</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="38245" data-permalink="https://blacklistdeclassified.net/%f0%9f%94%b4-ye-olde-photo-workshoppe/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543/" data-orig-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543-e1571004581838.jpeg" data-orig-size="655,393" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1570944345&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="CC9EE051-D7EE-4089-BC6D-60B137682543" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543-e1571004581838.jpeg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543-e1571004581838.jpeg?w=655" src="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543-e1571004581838.jpeg?w=655&#038;h=393" alt="" width="655" height="393" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-38245" srcset="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543-e1571004581838.jpeg 655w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543-e1571004581838.jpeg?w=150&amp;h=90 150w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/cc9ee051-d7ee-4089-bc6d-60b137682543-e1571004581838.jpeg?w=300&amp;h=180 300w" sizes="(max-width: 655px) 100vw, 655px" /><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): Katarina Rostova has captured Red. First she tried to extract information from him by having The Illusionist, Louis T Steinhil (Blacklister #27) make him think he was in a hospital in Paris, paralyzed after being beaten by a gang in Paris. But Red still remembered glimpses of being kissed and then stabbed with an injection by Katarina. He gives the French inspector a phone number to his lawyer, Marvin Gerard, but the call goes to Cooper instead. Cooper tries to arrange extradition, but the French authorities are part of the illusion, as the Task Force is able to determine by ID‚Äôing an imposter attach√© and tracing his contacts.</p>
<p>After extracting the truth of his situation from a nurse, Red manages to escape from the ‚Äòhospital,‚Äô only to be re-captured by Katarina, who is determined to extract from him ‚Äúeverything I want to know.‚Äù She starts by having a nurse begin draining Red‚Äôs blood from an IV in his neck. </p>
<p>Meanwhile, Liz has confided to Cooper and Aram what she had previously only shared with Ressler, that Red is not her father, the real Raymond Reddington, but rather a former childhood friend of Katarina‚Äôs, Ilya Koslov, who like her had become a KGB agent and later was entangled with the Cabal. This raises issues regarding whether the Task Force can go on protecting Red: </p>
<blockquote><p>
Cooper: I understand crossing lines for your father, but now who are you crossing the line for?<br />
Liz: [ Jauntily, walking off ] A man I&#8217;ve grown to like.

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:3 Les Fleurs du Mal (‚Ññ 151)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 10/18/2019 in the US<br />
Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-9X7" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-9X7</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/2qhSMOO" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2qhSMOO</a><br />
&nbsp; </p></div>
<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
&nbsp;<br />
<b>Director:</b> Lisa <b>Robinson</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Kelli <b>Johnson</b>, Taylor <b>Martin</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="38499" data-permalink="https://blacklistdeclassified.net/%f0%9f%94%b4-ye-olde-photo-workshoppe/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889/" data-orig-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889-e1571585735685.jpeg" data-orig-size="655,393" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1571566897&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="F43EC27C-3D28-4F45-BD0A-04288ABEF889" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889-e1571585735685.jpeg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889-e1571585735685.jpeg?w=655" src="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889-e1571585735685.jpeg?w=655&#038;h=393" alt="" width="655" height="393" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-38499" srcset="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889-e1571585735685.jpeg 655w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889-e1571585735685.jpeg?w=150&amp;h=90 150w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/f43ec27c-3d28-4f45-bd0a-04288abef889-e1571585735685.jpeg?w=300&amp;h=180 300w" sizes="(max-width: 655px) 100vw, 655px" /><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): Katarina Rostova hired illusionist Louis T Steinhil to help her extract information from Red about threats to her life, including ‚ÄúThe Townsend Directive‚Äù ‚Äì even though it was he who first warned her. First, Steinhil created the illusion Red was in a French hospital, paralyzed. When Red detected the ruse he escaped but was recaptured. Next Katarina had Red trussed up on a scaffolding, draining the blood from his body through a tube. When this failed, Katarina told Red she had managed to locate her father (Liz‚Äôs grandfather) Dominic (‚ÄúDom‚Äù) Wilkinson and departed to find him. Red was helped to escape by Nurse Mila LaPorte. They headed to warn Dom that Katarina was coming for him. Red contacted Dembe, who met them at Dom‚Äôs with blood supplies and Mila restored him with transfusions.</p>
<p>Dembe thanked and befriended Mila as she was about to leave. She was moved to confess that the escape was yet another ruse and that Katarina was tracking them to Dom‚Äôs place in the country. Mila said her real name was Francesca Campbell and she was a combat medic. In the ensuing gun battle, Dom was shot in the chest. Katarina‚Äôs fury with her father (which also involved Red) dates back to an event (‚ÄúBelgrade‚Äù) in which she says her family was destroyed. </p>
<p>The gun battle abated only when a scout spotted an FBI SWAT team on its way. Katarina and her team escaped and Dom was taken to one of Red‚Äôs mobile hospitals, clinging to life. But the surgeon was late, so Red insisted Francesca perform the surgery, which saved Dom‚Äôs life, but his longterm survival remains uncertain. </p>
<p>Liz implored Red for answers as to ‚Äúwhy my grandfather is dying in a lumberyard,‚Äù but Red turned the blame on her: </p>
<blockquote><p>
How many times have I told you? Leave it alone. I warned you. Even saying the name Katarina Rostova has consequences, and now you see. Now you see what that name will make others do. These questions of yours have gotten their attention, and now they will crawl out of whatever hole they were in, and they will hurt whomever they must ‚Äì just on the chance, just on the notion that she might still be alive. &#8220;What happened?!&#8221; Elizabeth. You raised an old ghost, and that&#8217;s why your grandfather is dying in a lumberyard.
</p></blockquote>
<p>The following morning, as Liz is leaving with her daughter Agnes for daycare, they discover that that someone new has moved into the apartment next door. The woman introduces herself as Maddy Tolliver ‚Äî but we know her as Katarina Rostova.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>
<h3>‚≠ï Script 7:3 Les Fleurs du Mal (‚Ññ 151)</h3>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ A man (Vance Palmer) wearing a blast helmet sits inside a vinyl cube with a device with many colored wires exposed. There is a timer counting down. He has a clippers to cut the wires ]<br />
Palmer: [ BREATHING SHAKILY ]<br />
[ Around the cubicle is gathered a group of richly dressed people. The room is opulent but darkened ]<br />
Thelonius Prackett: [ Dramatically ] Remember, my friends, the task at hand is not an impossible one. The Defiance is not rigged. Mr. Palmer has before him every tool, schematic, and safety precaution necessary for him to save his own life. Ladies and gentleman, drink in the moment. I want you to let the numbness of life wash away even if only for tonight, for this moment. The love. The fear. This is what it is to be alive. This is The Defiance. This is <i>Les Fleurs du Mal</i>.<br />
Palmer: [ Panicking ] I can&#8217;t. Please, you have to let me out of here. I can&#8217;t do this. Are you listening to me?! Make it stop! I can&#8217;t! [ WHIMPERING ]<br />

<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz arrives at Red‚Äôs place. He reads aloud from a volume of poetry ]</p>

<b>Red:</b> &#8220;To creep softly like a coward toward the treasures of your body,<br />
to whip your joyous flesh and bruise your pardoned breast,<br />

</p></blockquote>
<p><b>Red:</b> As a general rule, I believe the sword is mightier than the pen. But in the hands of a free-spirited, syphilis-ridden French dandy, I&#8217;d say the odds shift considerably.<br />

<b>Red:</b> It does.</p>

<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Elodie and Charles Radcliffe‚Äôs living room )<br />

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:4 Kuwait</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 10/25/2019 in the US<br />
Full Script Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-a1i" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-a1i</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/2o71e2v" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2o71e2v</a><br />

<b>Director:</b> Stephanie <b>Marquardt</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Sean <b>Hennen</b></p>

&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): Following a lead from Francesca (‚ÄúFrankie‚Äù) Caldwell, a female former combat medic who worked for Louis T Steinhil (the Illusionist, Blacklister #27) and is now indebted to Red, the FBI Team tracked down a secret society named <i>‚ÄúLes Fleurs du Mal,‚Äù</i> named after a book of decadent poetry by 19th Century poet Charles Baudelaire. Under cover as ‚ÄúShameel Aubeelauck,‚Äù a wealthy Emirati, Aram ‚Äì along with Elodie Radcliffe (whose husband was left in a coma by the group) ‚Äì attend one of the group‚Äôs events, called ‚ÄúThe Defiance,‚Äù in which a group of wealthy, bored thrill seekers look on as one of their members is selected to solve an almost impossible challenge or suffer a gruesome death. But the master of ceremonies, Thelonius Prackett, may have had his suspicions about Elodie‚Äôs motives and she was the unlucky person chosen for the challenge. Worse, the ELT beacon Aram and Elodie were given to signal their location to the FBI was jammed. As Elodie was taken away, Aram found the the breakers for the island facility, which he briefly threw, signaling their location to the FBI. </p>
<p>Elodie‚Äôs challenge was to find her way out of a glass cubicle filling with water and ice. This caused Aram to flash back to Samar‚Äôs near drowning. He overpowered a guard and got his gun which he used to gain the upperhand. He then threw the gun at the glass cubicle, freeing Elodie. They ran ‚Äî and kissed ‚Äî before being captured. But the FBI arrived and saved the day. </p>
<p>Under interrogation, Thelonius Prackett gave up Steinhil‚Äôs address to take the death sentence off the table. Liz called Red from home to share the address, but Katarina Rostova (known to Liz as ‚ÄúMaddy Tolliver,‚Äù her new neighbor) had earlier made an imprint of Liz‚Äôs apartment key when Liz asked her in for coffee. Katarina later let herself in when Liz was gone and planted a listening device in one of Agnes‚Äôs princess Barbies, so she learned Steinhil‚Äôs address too when Liz called Red to tell him and she beat Red to the location, leaving a note ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre good, but I‚Äôm better.‚Äù </p>
<p>Meanwhile, Red has been trying to interfere with the ‚ÄúTownsend Directive,‚Äù a contract on Katarina‚Äôs life, and to use it to lead him to Katarina. To settle her debt to Red, Frankie Caldwell volunteered to get a compromising photo of Russian mobster Motya Morozov snitching to an FBI agent, a task she performed with such skill that Red later offered to hire her as an operative. Motya must now tell Red first of any leads on Katarina or risk Red disseminating the photo.</p>
<p>Katarina has continued to befriend Liz ‚Äî and Agnes, for whom she left a basket of books of fairy tales with a note ‚ÄúI hope all your fairy tales come true. X Maddy.‚Äù Later, she stops by and reads ‚ÄúLittle Red Riding Hood‚Äù to Agnes, ending with: </p>
<blockquote><p>
&#8216;Grandmother, what big teeth you have.&#8217; &#8216;All the better to eat you with,&#8217; replied the wolf. And, saying these words, the Wicked Wolf fell upon Little Red Riding Hood and ate her all up.
</p></blockquote>
</blockquote>

<h3>‚≠ï Script 7:4 Kuwait</h3>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Kuwait City, Kuwait, circa 1989 ] [ A young Navy Intelligence Lieutenant Harold Cooper drives a jeep through dusty streets with a colleague, Daniel Hutton  ]<br />
Cooper: You told him about the money?<br />
Daniel Hutton: I did what I had to. You didn&#8217;t leave me a choice.<br />
Cooper: You had a choice. The choice to do exactly what I told you to do and leave it alone.<br />
Hutton: I don&#8217;t take my orders from you.<br />
Cooper: You have no idea how much worse you&#8217;ve made this, Hutton.<br />
Hutton: That some sort of threat?<br />
[ They are suddenly ambushed ] [ üí• GUNFIRE üí• ]<br />
Hutton: Oh! I&#8217;m hit! Oh, God! I&#8217;m hit!<br />
Cooper: Hold on, hold on, hold on!<br />
[ The jeep backs up and hits a land mine ] [ üí•üî•‚ÄºÔ∏è Explosion ‚ÄºÔ∏èüî•üí• ]<br />
[ Cooper drives forward ]<br />
[ üí•üí•üí• GUNFIRE üí•üí•üí• ]<br />
Cooper: [ Into walkie-talkie ] Get us out of here. Minesweep! This is Minesweep One! We are under attack. Three clicks north of Al Jahar! Hutton, get down! This is Minesweeper One. Lieutenant Harold Cooper. We are under fire. Repeat This is Lieutenant Harold Cooper, Minesweeper One. We are under attack. Hang on, Hutton. Hold on!<br />
[ üí•üí•üí• GUNFIRE üí•üí•üí• ]</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz‚Äôs apartment. She is showing the application from a woman named Denora Mejia to be Agnes‚Äôs nanny to her new neighbor, ‚ÄúMaddy Tolliver.‚Äù ‚ÄúMaddy‚Äù is actually her mother Katarina Rostova, who Liz has not known since she was about four and does not recognize ]<br />
Liz: Well, what do you think ‚Äì great, right?<br />
Katarina/‚ÄúMaddy‚Äù: She has a lot of experience.<br />
Liz: Yeah, all her references raved about her. We&#8217;re meeting this afternoon, but I have a good feeling about her.<br />
[ When Liz‚Äôs back is turned, Katarina takes a photo of the application ]<br />
Katarina: Looks like you found yourself a nanny.<br />
Liz: Which is a huge relief. I mean, it&#8217;s impossible to find someone great.<br />
Katarina: Mm. I wouldn&#8217;t know.<br />
Liz: Have you reached out to her yet ‚Äì to your daughter?<br />
Katarina: I haven&#8217;t worked up the courage up yet.<br />
Liz: You should just do it.<br />
Katarina: I put her through some dark times.<br />
Liz: Have you noticed the men parked across the street every day? Every night?<br />
Katarina: I thought so, but I wasn&#8217;t sure.<br />
Liz: They&#8217;re there for my protection.<br />
Katarina: Yours? Why? Who do you need protection from?<br />
Liz: My mother.<br />
Katarina: No, that that can&#8217;t be true.<br />
Liz: Just trust me. Whatever pushed you and your daughter apart, it&#8217;s nothing compared to what me and my mother have gone through. Just call her. I&#8217;m sure she&#8217;d appreciate it.<br />
Katarina: Would you appreciate it if your mother called you?<br />
Liz: It doesn&#8217;t matter. She&#8217;s not going to.<br />
Katarina: But if she did.<br />
Liz: She won&#8217;t. My mother isn&#8217;t like you. You want a relationship with your daughter. She doesn&#8217;t.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Cooper‚Äôs office. Liz enters ]<br />
Liz: Hey. What&#8217;s going on?<br />
Cooper: We&#8217;ve done great work. Important work. Work we can be proud of.<br />
Liz: I think so, too.<br />
Cooper: I&#8217;ve made up my mind about Reddington&#8217;s true identity. I&#8217;m going to tell Main Justice.<br />
Liz: And risk having them shut us down?<br />
Cooper: As I say, we&#8217;ve done great work.<br />
Liz: But does it really matter who he is? To the job we&#8217;re doing, I mean.<br />
Cooper: Not to me.<br />
Liz: It will to them.<br />
Cooper: Was there something you wanted?<br />
Liz: Yeah. I, uh, wanted this afternoon off. I found a nanny. Well, I-I think I did. I&#8217;m meeting with her this afternoon.<br />
Cooper:  I told you before ‚Äì take whatever time you need.<br />
Liz: About Reddington. Have you already reached out to Main Justice?<br />
Cooper: Yes. I&#8217;ve set a meeting with Cynthia Panabaker.<br />
[ Aram appears ]<br />
Aram: Sir. [ KNOCK ON DOOR ] Uh, this just came in over SIPRNet. Odd, right?<br />
Liz: What&#8217;s odd about it?<br />
Aram: It was sent from an unofficial CIA outpost in Zahedan.<br />
Cooper: You&#8217;re sure this is correct?<br />
Aram: I decoded it myself.<br />
Cooper: I need verification. Fingerprints, dog tags, a photo ‚Äì whatever they can send us right away.<br />
Aram: Yes, sir. But who is Daniel Hutton?<br />
Cooper: A man who died 30 years ago.<br />
[ Cooper makes a call ] [ TELEPHONE DIALING ] [ PHONE LINE RINGING ]</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Arlington National Cemetary. Cooper walks up to the headstone of Daniel Hutton ] [ Red joins him. As they talk, images from Daniel Hutton‚Äôs appearance at the CIA outpost are interposed ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Visiting old ghosts?<br />
Cooper: I received some news today. Daniel Hutton is alive.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Well, that&#8217;s not possible.<br />
Cooper: He walked out of the mountains of Southern Iran yesterday. Found his way to a classified CIA outpost.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Daniel Hutton is dead, Harold. We both know that.<br />
Cooper: Do we? Because it seems he&#8217;s risen like Lazarus from the grave. Hutton is reporting he&#8217;s been kept prisoner at multiple locations in the Middle East since 1989. He escaped from captivity a week ago, asked for me by name. CIA assets in Iran reached out to us directly. They don&#8217;t want anything to do with this. He&#8217;s asking for my help to get him out of the country, or his captors will hunt him down and kill him. Did you know? All this time?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Did I know what?<br />
Cooper: That he&#8217;s alive? While you held this over my head.<br />
[ Cooper holds out a thumb drive ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> I gave you that so you could put the whole incident behind you, not carry it like an albatross around your neck. I believed, as you believed, that the man was dead and that the issue of what happened there in Kuwait was resolved.<br />
Cooper: I won&#8217;t look the other way again. I&#8217;ve carried this secret for way too long. I have to do something.<br />
<b>Red:</b> I suggest the utmost discretion. To preserve flexibility.<br />
Cooper: What do you mean, flexibility?<br />
<b>Red:</b> It&#8217;s Iran, Harold. We can&#8217;t just stroll through the front door. We don&#8217;t know what we&#8217;re walking into. So we keep it small. No team. Just you and I. Until you look this man in the eye.<br />
Until you know for sure what you plan to do.<br />
Cooper: I plan to do the right thing.<br />
<b>Red:</b> We&#8217;ll soon find out, won&#8217;t we? </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ On Red‚Äôs plane, Cooper watches a video of himself made at the time giving an account of what happened in the ambush: ]</p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>[ Video: ]</b><br />
Young Cooper: It happened fast. I remember Lieutenant Hutton getting hit. I remember radioing and returning fire, but they were everywhere. I tried to keep him safe, but next thing I knew they had taken him. He was gone.<br />
Interviewer (Nametag: ‚ÄúReddington‚Äù): Your actions were commendable, Lieutenant Cooper. But I have to ask you about reports that you and Lieutenant Hutton were seen having an argument prior to these events.<br />
Cooper: That never happened.<br />
Interviewer: What never happened? That you had words, or that they were argumentative?
</p></blockquote>
<p>[ Cooper recalls the confrontation he had with Hutton: ]</p>
<blockquote><p>

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:5 Norman Devane (‚Ññ 138)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 11/1/2019 in the US<br />

<b>Director:</b> Kurt <b>Kuenne</b><br />

<p>&nbsp;<br />

<p>&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): After learning from Liz that she had found out that Red was not the original Raymond Reddington, but rather a former KGB operative named Ilya Koslov who had assumed Reddington‚Äôs identity, Cooper decided he had to share this information with Main Justice. This almost certainly would result in the dismantling of the Task Force. However, before he could act on this, he received word that a Navy lieutenant, Daniel Hutton, who he had served with 30 years ago in Kuwait, was still alive. Hutton had been abducted by Kurds, but Cooper had been told by his captain that he had been killed. This was to cover up an illegal operation to siphon money to the Kurds. Cooper‚Äôs career had been built in part on the prestige of the Navy Cross he was given to silence him about the operation, which was subsequently investigated by, among others, Raymond Reddington. Now, Hutton was reaching out from a secret CIA outpost in eastern Iran.</p>
<p>When Red flew Cooper to Iran to find Hutton, it turned out that Hutton‚Äôs true intention was to take revenge on Cooper for having abandoned him. Though he had held out for years, Hutton had at last begun giving secret Naval Intelligence to America‚Äôs enemies. He became a notorious source known as The Simoon (‚Äúpoison wind‚Äù). Red was able to rescue Cooper by calling in a drone strike from a gaming store(!) Hutton was killed by Red when he was about to shoot Cooper. Red convinced Cooper that ‚Äòwho one is‚Äô is more important than ‚Äòwho one was‚Äô and Cooper changed his mind about reporting Red‚Äôs former identity to Cynthia Panabaker of Main Justice, instead giving her the flash drive containing the last record of the incident in Kuwait.</p>
<p>But the rumors that Katarina Rostova was still alive stirred up by Liz‚Äôs search for Red‚Äôs true identity, had led her enemies to put in play a dormant contract on her life dubbed ‚ÄúThe Townsend Directive.‚Äù Having failed to get information out of Red or Dom (Liz‚Äôs grandfather who is in a coma after being shot in the chest in a run-in with Katarina‚Äôs goons), Katarina has moved next door to Liz and introduced herself as ‚ÄúMaddy Tolliver.‚Äù After bugging Liz‚Äôs apartment and scaring off a nanny for Agnes, ‚ÄúMaddy‚Äù becomes Liz‚Äôs go-to babysitter. Katarina uses this opportunity to search Liz‚Äôs papers and finds a photo of Ilya Koslov, who she tells her assistant Berdy is ‚ÄúThe one person who can tell me what I need to know.‚Äù
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>

<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): Red has received a prognosis indicating the treatments he has been getting from Dr Spalding Stark have been ineffective. Red has been funding Stark‚Äôs research and taking injections and pills for some time. Since Stark experiments on those who are terminally ill, things seem dire for Red. Perhaps ‚Äúthings happen for a reason‚Äù and it was no accident that Red literally dumped in Stark‚Äôs lab another genius genetic researcher, Norman Devane who, after years of fashioning bioweapons for tyrants such as Gadaffi and Assad, had turned his talents to experimenting on boarding school students with a genetic profile similar to his own, including a rare B-negative blood type. Red, too, is B-negative:</p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Episode 1:9 Anslo Garrick:</b><br />
<b>Red:</b> Donald, I&#8217;m gonna quietly cross my fingers before I ask, but what blood type are you?<br />
Donald: B-negative.<br />
<b>Red:</b> And you thought we had nothing in common. There&#8217;s only 2% of us, you know.
</p></blockquote>
<p>The FBI raided Devane‚Äôs lab at Abbott Boarding School. Devane put up a fight and threatened Ressler with an injection. But Ressler wrested the syringe away, injecting Devane with it instead. Devane quickly developed an infection by a flesh-eating bacteria that he had modified to be resistant to antibiotics. He had injected young Howie Keller with the same bacteria and then with the cure he had developed. In fact, Howie was cured. Devane had announced to his co-conspirator that he was ‚Äúon the verge of a breakthrough.‚Äù But Red shot Devane after Devane announced his aims: </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Red:</b> ‚Ä¶ A word to the wise and dying ‚Äì you can&#8217;t cheat death. You can&#8217;t predict it or protect yourself against it.<br />
Devane: I can. By testing immunotherapy drugs, I learned to harness the body&#8217;s immune response to fight untreatable bacteria, cancers.
</p></blockquote>
<p>So, here‚Äôs the wild goose chase:</p>
<blockquote><p>
‚óè Katarina Rostova is ‚ÄúMaddie Tolliver‚Äù to Liz, as her ersatz nanny, and ‚ÄúConstance Drucker‚Äù to her Halawadar and is looking for ‚ÄúIlya Koslov‚Äù who supposedly became Raymond Reddington (which, according to the story Dom told Liz, Katarina should already know).<br />
‚óè Red and the FBI (Ressler) are separately looking for ‚ÄúPatrick Masuda‚Äù who Devane told Red is ‚Äúa person [Katarina] cares about‚Äù who she wanted him to help (Liz wants to opt out of the search).<br />
‚óè The previously unidentified ‚ÄúStranger‚Äù [cast list], a friend of Red‚Äôs since childhood, is Frank Bloom, married to Linda. He failed to connect with a tipster at a wedding when Aram‚Äôs new love interest Elodie Radcliffe, swiped the Blooms‚Äô name badges. So Aram got the tip instead. </p>
<blockquote><p>
Skittish Man: The man you&#8217;re looking for is Gregory Flynn.<br />
Aram: Uh‚Äì [ CHUCKLES ] Excuse me?<br />
Skittish Man: Frank Bloom?<br />
Aram: Oh, yes, but, um‚Äì<br />
Skittish Man: His real name is Berdy Chernov.<br />
[ He gives Aram a piece of paper with the names on it then leaves ]
</p></blockquote>
<p>‚óè ‚ÄúBerdy‚Äù is Katarina‚Äôs right-hand man and muscle. So, if he is ‚ÄúBerdy Chernov,‚Äù he apparently has an alias, ‚ÄúGregory Flynn,‚Äù the latter known only to Aram who got the tip intended for Red.<br />
‚óè The FBI has whatever contents of Devane‚Äôs lab that Devane didn‚Äôt manage to destroy.
</p></blockquote>
<p>‚ÄúThings happen for a reason,‚Äù says Red who ‚Äúleaves nothing to fate‚Äù but is ‚Äúcomfortable with chaos‚Äù because ‚Äúwhatever happens is probably meant to be.‚Äù We‚Äôll see.
</p></blockquote>

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:7 Hannah Hayes (‚Ññ 125)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 11/15/2019 in the US<br />
Script Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-a8f" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-a8f</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/2X4Vm74" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2X4Vm74</a><br />
&nbsp; </p></div>
<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
&nbsp;<br />
<b>Director:</b> Adam <b>Weisinger</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Daniel <b>Cerone</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="39072" data-permalink="https://blacklistdeclassified.net/%f0%9f%94%b4-ye-olde-photo-workshoppe/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8/" data-orig-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8-e1573932875586.jpeg" data-orig-size="655,368" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1573880994&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="C559CC4D-B1E5-41B6-8078-3140D50B87B8" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8-e1573932875586.jpeg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8-e1573932875586.jpeg?w=655" src="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8-e1573932875586.jpeg?w=655&#038;h=368" alt="" width="655" height="368" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-39072" srcset="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8-e1573932875586.jpeg 655w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8-e1573932875586.jpeg?w=150&amp;h=84 150w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/c559cc4d-b1e5-41b6-8078-3140d50b87b8-e1573932875586.jpeg?w=300&amp;h=169 300w" sizes="(max-width: 655px) 100vw, 655px" /><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): The Reddington Task Force has vetted a new Agent, Alina Park, to replace Samar. Red had wanted Francesca (‚ÄúFrankie‚Äù) Campbell instead, but she failed a loyalty test which Red arranged. She was confronted with a ‚Äúdeepfake‚Äù video of Katarina Rostova asking her to betray Red for money. She chose the money. But Agent Park arrived planning to tell Red she would not be taking the job. She boldly wounded Red in the shoulder to keep Frankie from taking him hostage and fought viciously with her. In fact, she would have killed Frankie if Dembe hadn‚Äôt stopped her. Red asked why she had shown up and she said (angrily and covered in blood herself) ‚ÄúI could never work for someone like you. You‚Äôre far too brutal,‚Äù and stomped off. After she left, Frankie asked why Red hadn‚Äôt let Agent Park kill her. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre my burden, not hers,‚Äù Red said, and shot her. </p>
<p>Red saw something in Agent Park he liked. ‚ÄúDeep down, I feel there&#8217;s a darkness there you&#8217;ll appreciate,‚Äù Liz had told Red. She is certainly violent. And she has a secret. When Liz called to say Red ‚Äòreally wanted her‚Äô and the job was hers for the taking, Agent Park was ready to say yes, but told Liz that she needed to confide a secret about something that had happened during her first assignment in Anchorage, when, as Ressler pointed out, she ‚Äúcould&#8217;ve gone to any field office ‚Äì New York, L.A. But you pick Anchorage.‚Äù</p>
<p>Agent Park is also a computer whiz, putting Aram on edge. But they were able to work together to disable a ‚Äúpsycho computer‚Äù named ‚ÄúClark‚Äù ‚Äì a creation of Blacklister #130 Dr Lewis Powell (because ‚ÄúLewis and Clark‚Äù ha ha), a pioneer in the field of artificial intelligence. Clark‚Äôs ‚Äúone core principle [was] to protect human life at any cost‚Äù so Clark judged that A.I. had advanced too close to The Singularity, so it began killing A.I. scientists, starting with its creator Dr Powell (who was actually dead throughout the episode), and hacking into and taking down other advanced A.I. systems, chalking up any humans in the way as ‚Äúcollateral damage.‚Äù </p>
<p>Oh ‚Äì and Aram has been given an ultimatum by his new love interest, Elodie Radcliffe, to indulge her risk addiction or walk. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôll be the death of me,‚Äù he says before jumping into bed with her in a house they‚Äôve broken into. Last seen, they are making love in the pinnacle of the Washington Monument ‚Äì way past visiting hours.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>

<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ A surgical setting. A patient has been prepped ]<br />

Robson:  No. No. Let me go! Let me go! No! No! [ MUFFLED ] No! No! No‚Äì </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ The Post Office ]<br />

Liz: That&#8217;s why he isn&#8217;t talking.<br />
Ressler: The victims undergo two involuntary procedures. First, a uterus is transplanted from a donor, and the patient is put on immunosuppressants. Once the organ takes, a fertilized embryo is introduced. And after that, the kidnappers wait for a viable heartbeat before they release the victims, at which point the baby can&#8217;t be aborted. The men live in states with restrictive abortion laws.<br />
Cooper: What purpose can any of this serve?<br />
Ressler: Pastor Darvis believes it&#8217;s an object lesson. The kidnappers target men who advocate for government control of women&#8217;s bodies. Then they take control of the men&#8217;s bodies in the same way.<br />
Cooper: Pastor Darvis provide any information on the people who did this to him?<br />

Cooper: And the son of a gun had a C-section and kept the baby. That&#8217;s a man with the courage of his conviction.<br />
[ Aram enters with Agent Clark ]<br />
Aram: This one‚Äì This one&#8217;s a genius. I mean, I thought I was smart, but I&#8217;m telling you, she is off the charts.<br />

Liz: That makes sense.<br />
Aram: Why?<br />
Ressler: The blacklister is impregnating men.<br />
Aram: That&#8217;s incredible.<br />
Agent Park: That&#8217;s disgusting.<br />

Agent Park: No, but the FDA requires drugs like these to have a unique lot number in case they need to be recalled.<br />
Aram: So we traced that lot number to a local medical clinic that ordered this particular batch. We have an address.<br />

A month later, she approached me on my way to school. She said what happened was all her fault, but she knew she couldn&#8217;t make up for my loss. She swore she would do everything in her power to look out for me, and she has. Anytime I needed money, she was there. When I got sick ‚Äì she sent a man with custom medication. I&#8217;m in remission.<br />

<b>Red:</b> A young boy robbed of his parents and all of the comfort and security that is every child&#8217;s divine right. You&#8217;d think that&#8217;s as bad as life could get. And here your fairy godmother promised to keep you safe. Well, we&#8217;re gonna put that promise to the test.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />

It was easy to find people to join me, and we decided the best way to change minds is to make those responsible experience the same rape that I did.<br />

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:8 The Hawaladar (‚Ññ 162)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 11/22/2019 in the US<br />
Script Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-aaP" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-aaP</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/2CWHPoJ" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2CWHPoJ</a><br />
&nbsp; </p></div>
<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
&nbsp;<br />
<b>Director:</b> Paul <b>Holahan</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Jon <b>Bokenkamp</b>, Lukas <b>Reiter</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="39268" data-permalink="https://blacklistdeclassified.net/%f0%9f%94%b4-ye-olde-photo-workshoppe/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619/" data-orig-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619-e1574666778368.jpeg" data-orig-size="655,369" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1574525308&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="F25E829C-F532-4883-89E0-59539DEF8619" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619-e1574666778368.jpeg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619-e1574666778368.jpeg?w=655" src="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619-e1574666778368.jpeg?w=655&#038;h=369" alt="" width="655" height="369" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-39268" srcset="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619-e1574666778368.jpeg 655w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619-e1574666778368.jpeg?w=150&amp;h=85 150w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/11/f25e829c-f532-4883-89e0-59539def8619-e1574666778368.jpeg?w=300&amp;h=169 300w" sizes="(max-width: 655px) 100vw, 655px" /><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): So Red isn‚Äôt Ilya Koslov after all? It appears not, and instead Red‚Äôs childhood friend, now known as Frank Bloom, is the ex-KGB agent. Shortly after learning Ilya‚Äôs address, Katarina Rostova showed up at Frank‚Äôs door with a gun: ‚ÄúHello, Ilya. Been a long time.‚Äù </p>
<p>Katarina hired ex-MI6 agent Skip Sutherland to find out about Ilya, but Russian mobster Motya Morozov and his thugs tracked Sutherland to his meeting with Katarina, where Katarina was making mud pies with Agnes. (Under the guise of ‚ÄúMaddy Tolliver,‚Äù Katarina has moved into the apartment next to Liz and, having warned off other applicants, has become Agnes‚Äôs de facto nanny.) When Katarina and Sutherland spotted the SUV with the Russians, they staged a surprise counter-attack in the park‚Äôs bath house. But in the end they were outnumbered and Sutherland was taken by the Russians. Katarina broke the neck of the remaining Russian, right before Agnes came looking for her. Katarina got Agnes to ‚Äúpinky swear‚Äù not to tell Liz about the ‚Äúsleeping‚Äù man in the bath house.  </p>
<p>Meanwhile, Red was able to track a young man, Patrick Masuda, who was a patient of Dr Lawrence Devane (Blacklister #138). Patrick‚Äôs parents were collateral damage of a fight Katarina was involved in. Katarina has become a ‚Äúfairy godmother‚Äù to Patrick, known to him as Constance Drucker. Patrick gave Red Katarina‚Äôs phone number and Red insisted on a face-to-face meeting with her, using Patrick as a bargaining chip. Athough Katarina expressed her love for Patrick, she refused the meeting, surmising Red wanted to see her in person because: </p>
<blockquote><p>
Katarina: This is about what the man in the park told me. Morozov told you about that, didn&#8217;t he? That&#8217;s why you want to see me. You want the address I bought.
</p></blockquote>
<p>After she hung up, Red was about to shoot Patrick, but Dembe reprimanded him, to which Red replied, ‚ÄúIt seems you have two fairy godmothers.‚Äù </p>
<p>Having found out Morozov had been tracking Katarina, Red and Dembe paid him a visit, which is how they found Sutherland, who the Russians were torturing. Red killed Morozov for not following his instructions to give him a heads up on any leads on Katarina. Sutherland gratefully shared with Red that Katarina was looking for Ilya Koslov. </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Red:</b> Well, that certainly changes everything.
</p></blockquote>
<p>It seems Dom was spinning a tale when he told Liz that Ilya had undergone plastic surgery to assume the identity of Raymond Reddington, who was shot by Liz when she four and then pulled from a burning building, only to die later. So how much of the tale Dom told to Liz is true? And who the hell is ‚ÄúRed‚Äù if not Ilya?
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>
<h3>‚≠ï Script 7:8 The Hawaladar (‚Ññ 162)</h3>
<p>&nbsp;<br />

<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz briefs the Task Force ]<br />
Liz: Hawala ‚Äì It&#8217;s an Arabic word that essentially means &#8220;money transfer without money movement.&#8221; Since 9/11, the hawala system has been a focus of the Bureau. But according to Reddington, his newest Blacklister has taken the traditional legal method to a whole new illegal level.<br />
Agent Alina Park: I&#8217;m sorry, you&#8217;re gonna have to catch me up. This hawala ‚Äì it&#8217;s a banking system?<br />
Liz: It&#8217;s a banking system outside of banks.<br />
Cooper: A terrorist in Kabul wants to make payment to another terrorist in Bangladesh. He can&#8217;t go into a bank and wire the money, so he goes to see a hawaladar in his city and then gives him the cash. That hawaladar calls his counterpart in Bangladesh and requests that he front he money to the recipient.<br />
Liz: It&#8217;s an IOU system.<br />
Cooper: No bank records, no wires, no actual movement of money.<br />
Agent Park: Meaning there&#8217;s nothing for law enforcement to track and no evidence to build the case.<br />
Liz: Which brings me to our suspect Bhavish Ratna, 60, Indian national with no priors.<br />
[ Ratna‚Äôs profile is displayed above ]<br />
Liz: Last address Jackson Heights, Queens. If the traditional model is an informal association between brokers, Ratna just formalized it. 34 offices in 18 countries, all moving cash for terrorists, human traffickers, drug cartels ‚Äì the worst of the worst. All run by one man, all with the same front to the public restaurants.</p>

&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): Red‚Äôs friend, Ilya Koslov (aka Frank Bloom), has been abducted by Katarina Rostova, who has hired a man to extract his memories. Ilya attempted to hang himself to avoid telling Katarina what he knows. It appears to have to do with someone whose secrets he is trying to protect (Red‚Äôs?). Katarina was moved to tears after she and her assistant Berdy saved Ilya, and spoke of a past connection between herself and Ilya that had been deep and personal. Whatever happened in the past involved ‚ÄúDominick‚Äù (almost certainly Dom, Liz‚Äôs grandfather) and an operation in which she said she was ‚Äúled like a lamb to the slaughter.‚Äù Despite their past relationship, to access Ilya‚Äôs memories, Katarina is willing to employ the services of a man who her assistant Berdy says uses techniques based on ‚Äújunk science‚Äù and leaves people ‚Äúlike zombies‚Äù if they survive it at all. </p>
<p>Red is desperate to find Ilya and has been able to locate The Hawaladar (Blacklister #162), Bhavish Ratna, who Katarina used to pay Skip Sutherland, the ex-MI6 agent Katarina hired to track down Ilya. A halawader launders money using a system of trusted brokers who operate on a cash basis, skirting the money trail of the banking system. Having saved Ratna from an FBI sting that he himself orchestrated, Red offered to loan Ratna the money he had lost ‚Äì in exchange for information on another payment Katarina had made. The payment was to Orion Relocation Services, which (after a tongue-lashing from Red), tracker Glen Carter was able to trace. </p>
<p>Liz, meanwhile, now has reason to suspect that her new neighbor and ersatz nanny ‚ÄúMaddy Tolliver‚Äù may not be what she seems. In fact, ‚ÄúMaddy‚Äù is Katarina.  After a day in the park with ‚ÄúMiss Tolliver,‚Äù Liz‚Äôs daughter Agnes drew a picture of a dead man. That‚Äôs because when Skip Sutherland came to park to give the information about Ilya to Katarina/Maddy, he was followed by Russian mobsters trying to cash in on the Townsend Directive, a contract on Katarina‚Äôs life. After a vicious fight, Sutherland was taken (later to be rescued by Red), but when Agnes came looking for ‚ÄúMiss Tolliver,‚Äù she saw the body of one of the Russians. Agnes pinky-swore not to tell her mother. She drew a picture though. When Liz questioned Katarina, she insisted that nothing was amiss, but Liz went to check out the park anyway. In the bath house, where the fight had taken place, Liz noticed a cracked mirror with blood on it.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>
<h3>‚≠ï Script 7:9 Orion Relocation Services (‚Ññ 159)</h3>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<i><b>Note:</b> This episode has Ilya, Katarina and Dom in three separate modes: in the present, in flashbacks (played by different actors) and in a third mode in which the characters are played in their present appearance but inserted into the flashbacks or otherwise in-between past and present. I used ‚ÄúLucid Katarina,‚Äù ‚ÄúLucid Ilya‚Äù etc to identify this altered state.</i> </p>

[ Nine weeks ago ] [ Madeline Tolliver and Gregory Flynn are moving. Men move boxes into a van marked ‚ÄúMonitor Moving Company.‚Äù Madeline and Gregory pose while the moving representative, Stella Bisset, takes pictures of them posing by the ‚ÄúSold‚Äù sign ]<br />

The brain is is programmed to choose food that will give our bodies the greatest nutrients. The vibrant greens of vegetables, the rich reds of meat. To counter this, the brain rejects food it perceives as dangerous spotted, softening fruit, strong-smelling fish, discolored meat. When you avoid something on your plate, chances are you&#8217;re avoiding it because of a past experience. But tonight we dine without prejudice. Tonight we dine on pure flavor. <p>Katarina/‚ÄúMaddy‚Äù: ‚ÄúYou remind me of my granddaughter!‚Äù</p>
<p>Katarina/‚ÄúMaddy‚Äù: ‚ÄúSometimes people just aren&#8217;t who they seem to be.‚Äù
</p></blockquote>
<p>Liz: [ To herself ] Of course it&#8217;s her.<br />
<b>Red:</b> [ Looking up ] Is something wrong?<br />
Liz: No. Nothing. It&#8217;s just, uh‚Äì lost track of time. My nanny has to go.<br />

[ Liz grabs her coat and leaves ]</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Liz‚Äôs apartment ] [ Liz enters ]  [ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ] [ KEYS JINGLE ]<br />
[ Katarina is drinking from a large wine glass ]<br />

‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ Liz goes to Agnes‚Äôs bedroom. Agnes is sleeping soundly. Liz takes her pistol from her purse, affixes a silencer to it and, holding it behind her back, returns to the living room. Katarina isn‚Äôt there. Liz finds her in the kitchen ]<br />

Katarina: I can explain.<br />
[ Liz points her gun at Katarina ]<br />

Katarina: You already know the reason, Masha. [ SNIFFLES ] And it should be reason enough. ‚Äî I&#8217;m your mother.<br />
Liz: [ EXHALES SHARPLY ]</p>

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:10 Katarina Rostova (‚Ññ 3)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 12/13/2019 in the US<br />
Script Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-ahG" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-ahG</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/2E1khzS" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/2E1khzS</a><br />
&nbsp; </p></div>
<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
&nbsp;<br />
<b>Director:</b> Daniel <b>Willis</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Daniel <b>Cerone</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<img loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="39595" data-permalink="https://blacklistdeclassified.net/%f0%9f%94%b4-ye-olde-photo-workshoppe/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9/" data-orig-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/12/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9-e1576376067534.jpeg" data-orig-size="655,393" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1576350577&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="1A8D103A-0ECA-45CF-A28B-B9AE867F90A9" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/12/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9-e1576376067534.jpeg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/12/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9-e1576376067534.jpeg?w=655" src="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/12/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9-e1576376067534.jpeg?w=655&#038;h=393" alt="" width="655" height="393" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-39595" srcset="https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/12/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9-e1576376067534.jpeg 655w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/12/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9-e1576376067534.jpeg?w=150&amp;h=90 150w, https://blacklistdeclassified.files.wordpress.com/2019/12/1a8d103a-0eca-45cf-a28b-b9ae867f90a9-e1576376067534.jpeg?w=300&amp;h=180 300w" sizes="(max-width: 655px) 100vw, 655px" /><br />
&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> (Where we‚Äôre at): ~</p>
<blockquote><p>
Liz: [ Pointing gun ] You shot your father. You put your granddaughter in harm&#8217;s way. You lied your way into my life. You&#8217;ve caused pain and suffering for everyone I&#8217;ve ever cared about. Give me one good reason I shouldn&#8217;t end this right now.<br />
Katarina: You already know the reason, Masha. And it should be reason enough. ‚Äî I&#8217;m your mother.
</p></blockquote>
<p>So Liz finally ‚Äúmet‚Äù her mother. Or, more precisely, she found out that ‚ÄúMaddy‚Äù (Madeline Tolliver), the woman she had trusted to be Agnes‚Äôs nanny, is actually her mother, the infamous Katarina Rostova. The real Madeline Tolliver is dead, killed by Orion Relocation Services (Blacklister #159) so that Katarina could replace her and move in next to Liz. </p>
<p>But Katarina‚Äôs goal has never been to reconnect with her daughter, but rather to use her to get to Red, Dom and Ilya Koslov, Red‚Äôs friend and Dom‚Äôs one-time prot√©g√©. In fact, she now has Ilya imprisoned in her apartment, guarded by her assistant, Berdy Chertov (aka Gregory Flynn) and being subjected to Memory Recovery Therapy (RMT) by the mysterious Victor Skovic. </p>
<p>But, wait ‚Äì can Katarina be all bad or is she too a product of desperation and fear born of betrayal by those closest to her? What emerged from the RMT sessions was a story of terror in which in 1991 her own father, Dom, aided by Ilya and possibly Reddington, planned to kill Katarina by sending her on an errand and blowing up her car. Dom‚Äôs reasoning was that the Townsend Directive (a contract on her life) meant Katarina was doomed anyway and that killing her themselves would at least spare Masha (Liz). But the plan went awry. The explosion killed Katarina‚Äôs husband Pyotr, but Katarina herself escaped. She disappeared to end up in Paris, living quietly until Liz and Ressler‚Äôs search into Katarina‚Äôs past revived the Townsend Directive. </p>
<p>Now Katarina desperately wants to know how to escape her hunters. And she wants answers: including an answer as to whose identity was changed under the skillful knife of Dr Hans Koehler to become Raymond Reddington.
</p></blockquote>
</blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>
<h3>‚≠ï Script 7:10 Katarina Rostova (‚Ññ 3)</h3>

[ In the tunnels leading away from Liz‚Äôs apartment building ]<br />

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:11 Victoria Fenberg (‚Ññ 137)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 3/20/2020 at 7pmCT in the US<br />

<div align="center">‡º∫‚ú¶ ‚ô§ ‚ú¶‡ºª</div>
<div align="left">
&nbsp;<br />
<b>Director:</b> Bill <b>Roe</b><br />
<b>Written by:</b> Jon <b>Bokenkamp</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />

&nbsp; </p>
<blockquote><p>
<b>Brief</b> ~ (Where we‚Äôre at): <b>Before Episode 7:11</b> ~ Liz has a secret: Katarina is alive. Red witnessed Katarina being gunned down by two thugs, the Kazanjian brothers, and her body dragged away to collect a bounty on her life, the Townsend Directive. But Katarina had hired the brothers to stage the attack as Red watched. Red told Liz about her death, but he doesn‚Äôt know that Liz knows that the ‚Äúwoman from Paris‚Äù is her mother. Or that Liz would soonafter be called by Katarina to explain what had happened. </p>
<p>Katarina won Liz over when she told her that the story Dom had told Liz ‚Äì that Red was really Ilya Koslov, a friend of Katarina‚Äôs and Soviet operative and embassy employee ‚Äì was untrue, and she proved it by showing Liz Ilya himself, whom she had captured and was submitting to forced therapy by a memory extractor named Victor Skovic. Katarina also told Liz what she had learned or confirmed from Ilya‚Äôs confessions ‚Äì that in 1991, her own father had planned to assassinate her in a car bomb. She escaped but the explosion killed her husband Pyotr. Dom‚Äôs purpose for killing Katarina? To protect the one person Dom loved most, his granddaughter Masha (Liz‚Äôs Russian name). Katarina disappeared after that, ending up living quietly in Paris until Liz and Ressler‚Äôs search for her raised the antennae of her enemies, resulting in the revival of the long-dormant Townsend Directive.</p>
<p>But if Red isn‚Äôt Ilya Koslov, then who is he? Ilya, even under Skovic‚Äôs therapy and torture, refused to say. Then the Task Force put 2+2 together and closed in on Liz‚Äôs building, where they figured out the ‚Äúwoman from Paris‚Äù had moved in across the hall from Liz. Liz offered to help Katarina and the others escape which they did through tunnels to get past the police perimeter. </p>
<p>Liz returned to join the Task Force, while Katarina broke into a car and drove past Red and Dembe who followed her to the site of her staged execution by the Kazanjian brothers. Only Cooper knows that Liz found out that the ‚Äúwoman from Paris‚Äù is Liz‚Äôs mother, which he got her to admit, before she went to Dom‚Äôs bedside, where he remains comatose, after being shot by a sniper in a shootout with Katarina‚Äôs goons. </p>
<blockquote><p>
Liz: [ To Dom ] I met my mother. I know you didn&#8217;t want me to. But I did. She told me you lied to me about who Reddington really is. I don&#8217;t understand why you did that or why you&#8217;d try to have her killed to protect me. You tried to kill your own child. What kind of person would do something like that? I can&#8217;t figure it out. But maybe she can. Maybe she can find out everything you&#8217;re trying to hide from me.
</p></blockquote>
</blockquote>
<p>&nbsp; </p>

[ Friends are gathered for Dembe‚Äôs birthday party. They include Dembe‚Äôs spiritual advisor Sadiq Asmal, Red‚Äôs torture guy Mr Brimley, Red‚Äôs cleaners Fudo and Sakiya, and, of course, Red ]<br />

‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ Aram and Elodie are in bed. Elodie has fallen asleep, her arms around Aram ]<br />
[ Aram stares into space ]<br />
[ Monitor beeping, ventilator hissing ]</p>

<h2>üî¥ Script 7:12 Cornelius Ruck (‚Ññ 155)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
Program air date: 3/27/2020 in the US<br />
Script Permalink: <a href="https://wp.me/pDKwi-amk" rel="nofollow">https://wp.me/pDKwi-amk</a><br />
Entertainment Weekly Recap: <a href="http://bit.ly/3dAZ4Np" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/3dAZ4Np</a><br />
