<blockquote><p>
Birch: [ Continuing voice-over ] ‚ÄîThere you will find all necessary financials, along with the dossier on your education, work, travel histories, and family life. Safe travels, and best of luck, Mr. Merwin.
</p></blockquote>
<p>[ Stanley Birch ends his call. Dembe gets out of a car that has pulled up to Birch‚Äôs chess shop ]<br />
Dembe: Our driver will take you to the tarmac. Edward will have you airborne in a matter of minutes.<br />
Birch: Thank you, Dembe. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
TAC Agent: [ On comms ] Bravo Team, we&#8217;ve got a visual on the chopper.<br />
Ressler: It&#8217;s got to be his exfil. We move now. Go, go, go!<br />
TAC Agent: [ On comms ] Clear. We have location confirmed.<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ The helicopter lands. Frank Merwin walks toward it ]<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ The TAC team makes its move ]<br />
‚Äî Move, move!<br />
Ressler: Stop! FBI!<br />
‚Äî Hold it!<br />
Ressler: Turn around, put your hands in the air! Hands!<br />
[ Merwin turns around but walks backwards toward the copter, until he is directly underneath its whirling blades ]<br />
Park: Stop! Stop moving. Hey, let me see hands!<br />
[ Agents in TAC gear with rifles move closer ]<br />
Ressler: Get on the ground! I said, get down! What&#8217;s in the briefcase? Put the briefcase down.<br />
[ Merwin raises one arm. With his left hand, he unlatches the briefcase. The thousands of bills and notes inside are sucked up by the helicopter blades and go flying everywhere ]<br />
[ Frank Merwin kneels down on the ground ] [ Indistinct shouting ] </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Text inset: <i>DOCTOR‚ÄôS ORDERS&#8230;</i> ] [ Dr Clemons talks to Red ]<br />
Dr Clemons: I&#8217;m not gonna minimize how serious this latest incident was or that it&#8217;s your second one this month. But adjusting the meds should take care of the tremors. Other than that, my prescription is rest. And honesty.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Are you my doctor or my conscience?<br />
Dr Clemons: Liz asked about your condition. I think it&#8217;s unhealthy to keep it secret from the people who care about you.<br />
<b>Red:</b> In my position, it&#8217;s not easy to know who cares and who wants to cut your throat. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red‚Äôs cellphone rings, beeps ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Tell me. </font><br />
Dembe: Raymond, he showed. Otte ‚Äì He&#8217;s here. She didn&#8217;t warn him off.<br />
[ Some distance away, a door opens. Wayne Otte gets out. He walks up to the Kazanjians ]<br />
Pasha Kazanjian: You have the account number?<br />
[ Otte gives Pasha a slip of paper ]<br />
Otte: She wants 75 grand to go to the first account. The balance goes to the second.<br />
[ Device beeping. The money is transferred ]<br />
Dembe: You underestimated Elizabeth. She&#8217;s on your side after all. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ An interrogation room at the Post Office ]<br />
Ressler: There&#8217;s no point in staying silent.<br />
Liz: Our agents are reviewing the documents we recovered as we speak.<br />
Ressler: We will make a case against you.<br />
Frank Merwin: In that case I&#8217;m not sure what you are so worried about.<br />
Ressler: We are not worried. We just want to let you know that we are working to put you behind bars for as long as is possible.<br />
Liz: If you cooperate, that couild change.<br />
Frank: Do either of you think that I&#8217;m really worried about your case?<br />
Ressler: You are going to prison Frank.<br />
Frank: For a while. I&#8217;ll get a few years. Good behavior, early parole, but soon enough I&#8217;ll be out, you know why? Because I&#8217;m very, very good in what I do.<br />
Ressler: Hmm. And yet you&#8217;re here with us.<br />
Frank: The only way you&#8217;ll be able to link me to any criminal wrongdoings is through any shred of financial data you may recover. But what you don&#8217;t seem to understand is that I move money for incredibly powerful people. Yes, some are cartels and hit men and white-collar criminals.<br />
Liz: Who want you dead because you stole from them.<br />
Frank: But I also represent corrupt cops, dirty politicians, judges for sale. All these people want to protect me, not because they care about me, because they care about themselves.<br />
Liz: I think we&#8217;re done here.<br />
Frank: Yes, I agree. But remember, I know you feds aren&#8217;t all as squeaky clean as you want the world to believe.<br />
Liz: What&#8217;s that supposed to mean?<br />
Frank: Probably nothing for either of you. You&#8217;re by the book, aboveboard. I&#8217;m sure there&#8217;s no way my arrest can implicate either of you. So, yes.<br />
Liz: Yes?<br />
Frank: Yes. We&#8217;re finished here. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Red exits the warehouse with the secret hospital and gets into the car with Dembe ]<br />
[ Siren wailing in distance ] [ Car door closes ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Otte gave you an account number?<br />
Dembe: Two, actually. Of her share of the bounty, $75,000 was transferred to the first account.  The rest went to her personally at the second number.<br />
<b>Red:</b> So she&#8217;s paying someone.<br />
Dembe: Otte didn&#8217;t know who.<br />
<b>Red:</b> And the Kazanjian brothers?<br />
Dembe: Chuck and Morgan took them for a drive.<br />
[ Red calls Liz ] [ Dialing, ringing ]<br />
<b>Red:</b> Elizabeth, I have a lead.<br />
Liz: You do? Tell me what happened.<br />
<b>Red:</b> Otte happened.<br />
Liz: Otte? He showed?<br />
<b>Red:</b> You sound surprised.<br />
Liz: No, I&#8217;m just‚Äì Was he helpful?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Tell me about Merwin.<br />
Liz: He refuses to cooperate. Otte ‚Äì Was he helpful?<br />
<b>Red:</b> Yes. Very. Thanks to you.<br />
Liz: I didn&#8217;t do anything.<br />
<b>Red:</b> No, but you could have. To be honest, I thought you would ‚Äì call her, take her side. But you didn&#8217;t. You took mine.<br />
Liz: Well, I‚Äì How you feeling?<br />
<b>Red:</b> [ Chuckles ] Happy as a seagull with a french fry. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
[ Knock on Katarina‚Äôs door ] [ Katarina opens it ] [ Liz walks in, past her ]<br />
Liz: I don&#8217;t understand. I warned you.<br />
Katarina: Yes.<br />
Liz: I told you Reddington knew about Otte and to call off the meeting.<br />
Katarina: You want to know why I didn&#8217;t.<br />
Liz: No, I want you to know what happened because you didn&#8217;t. Otte gave Reddington a way to find you.<br />
Katarina: I&#8217;m sure he did.<br />
Liz: Because you let him.<br />
Katarina: Which I did because I&#8217;m sure you were right. It was a test. To see if you were really in the middle. If I&#8217;d warned Otte off, Raymond would know that you weren&#8217;t. Sure, Otte gave him intel on how to find me, but I know that and can defend against it. But what Raymond doesn&#8217;t know ‚Äì is that you&#8217;re not in the middle. Are you?<br />
[ Liz sits down next to Katarina ]<br />
Liz: I&#8217;m on your side.<br />
Katarina: And he can&#8217;t defend against that.<br />
[ Cellphone buzzing ]<br />
[ Liz reads a text from Dr Clemons: ‚ÄúVitals good. Grandfather awake soon.‚Äù ]<br />
Katarina: Everything okay?<br />
Liz: Yeah. Everything&#8217;s good. </p>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<font color="‚Äú#FFCCCC‚Äù">[ Liz visits Dom ]<br />
Liz: Hey. Doctors say you&#8217;re gonna wake up soon. When you do, I need you to know the person who did this to you, my mother, I&#8217;m on her side now. I&#8217;m committed to helping her find the truth she&#8217;s looking for. Anyone who is in her way is in my way. That includes you. And that includes Reddington.<br />
‚ãò‚ãô<br />
[ Liz leaves Dom, then ascends flights of utility staircases in the old warehouse ]<br />
Liz: [ Voice-over ] It&#8217;s strange. I was afraid earlier of that darkness I was telling you about. I&#8217;ve always feared it. Ever since Reddington entered my life, I&#8217;ve worried that his darkness might somehow overtake me, that it might just swallow me whole.<br />
[ Liz emerges through a door onto the roof of the building ]<br />
Liz: But now that I&#8217;m here, I&#8217;m not afraid. In fact, I embrace this part of me and wherever it takes us on our way to the truth. You and me and Reddington, I&#8217;m at peace with that. I embrace that. I consider it my destiny.<br />
[ Liz goes to a ledge overlooking the darkened city. She puts one leg up on the ledge ]</font><br />
[ The Rolling Stones‚Äô ‚ô™ ‚ÄúPainted Black‚Äù plays ]<br />
<font color="‚Äú#FFCCCC‚Äù">[ Liz makes a call ] [ Cellphone beeps, dialing ] [ Line rings ]<br />
Liz: Mother, it&#8217;s me. I&#8217;m ready.<br />
[ Liz stands majestically looking over the city, her hair and coat blown by the wind ]</p>
<blockquote><p>
‚ô™ I see a red door, and I want it painted black ‚ô™
</p></blockquote>

var WPGroHo = {"my_hash":""};
</script>
<script type='text/javascript' src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/mu-plugins/gravatar-hovercards/wpgroho.js?m=1380573781h'></script>

	<script>
		//initialize and attach hovercards to all gravatars
		jQuery( document ).ready( function( $ ) {

			if (typeof Gravatar === "undefined"){
				return;
			}

			if ( typeof Gravatar.init !== "function" ) {
				return;
			}			

			Gravatar.profile_cb = function( hash, id ) {
				WPGroHo.syncProfileData( hash, id );
			};
			Gravatar.my_hash = WPGroHo.my_hash;
			Gravatar.init( 'body', '#wp-admin-bar-my-account' );
		});
	</script>

		<div style="display:none">
	</div>
